<h1>About this Sinatra app</h1>

<p>This is <code>app/hello.rb</code>, a real
   <a href="https://github.com/janbiedermann/sinatra">janbiedermann/sinatra</a>
   application running on Cloudflare Workers. The file would run
   unchanged on any Rack server; the Cloudflare adapter lives entirely
   in <code>lib/cloudflare_workers.rb</code> and doesn't leak through.</p>

<h2>How the pieces fit</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Sinatra DSL &rarr; Opal compiler &rarr; a 580 KiB gzipped ESM</li>
  <li>ERB templates in <code>views/*.erb</code> &rarr; precompiled by
      <code>bin/compile-erb</code> &rarr; <code>HomurabiTemplates</code>
      registry &rarr; <code>erb :name</code> helper</li>
  <li>Cloudflare bindings (<code>DB</code>, <code>KV</code>, <code>BUCKET</code>)
      exposed as plain Ruby wrappers in <code>env['cloudflare.DB']</code> etc.</li>
  <li>Routes that touch bindings use
      <code># await: true</code> and <code>.__await__</code> to bridge
      sync Sinatra to async Workers I/O</li>
</ul>

